verses.text_plain: O give thanks unto the Lord, for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.
verses.verse_html: 1O give thanks unto the Lord, for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.

verses.text_plain: Let the redeemed of the Lord say so, whom he hath redeemed from the hand of the enemy;
verses.verse_html: 2Let the redeemed of the Lord say so, whom he hath redeemed from the hand of the enemy;

verses.text_plain: And gathered them out of the lands, from the east, and from the west, from the north, and from the south.
verses.verse_html:
3And gathered them out of the lands, from the east, and from the west, from the north, and from the south. ▼
▼ south: Heb. sea

verses.text_plain: They wandered in the wilderness in a solitary way; they found no city to dwell in.
verses.verse_html: 4They wandered in the wilderness in a solitary way; they found no city to dwell in.

verses.text_plain: Hungry and thirsty, their soul fainted in them.
verses.verse_html: 5Hungry and thirsty, their soul fainted in them.

verses.text_plain: Then they cried unto the Lord in their trouble, and he delivered them out of their distresses.
verses.verse_html: 6Then they cried unto the Lord in their trouble, and he delivered them out of their distresses.

verses.text_plain: And he led them forth by the right way, that they might go to a city of habitation.
verses.verse_html: 7And he led them forth by the right way, that they might go to a city of habitation.

verses.text_plain: Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!
verses.verse_html: 8Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!

verses.text_plain: For he satisfieth the longing soul, and filleth the hungry soul with goodness.
verses.verse_html: 9For he satisfieth the longing soul, and filleth the hungry soul with goodness.

verses.text_plain: Such as sit in darkness and in the shadow of death, being bound in affliction and iron;
verses.verse_html: 10Such as sit in darkness and in the shadow of death, being bound in affliction and iron;

tokens.text: and in the shadow of death

verses.text_plain: Because they rebelled against the words of God, and contemned the counsel of the most High:
verses.verse_html: 11Because they rebelled against the words of God, and contemned the counsel of the most High:

verses.text_plain: Therefore he brought down their heart with labour; they fell down, and there was none to help.
verses.verse_html: 12Therefore he brought down their heart with labour; they fell down, and there was none to help.

verses.text_plain: Then they cried unto the Lord in their trouble, and he saved them out of their distresses.
verses.verse_html: 13Then they cried unto the Lord in their trouble, and he saved them out of their distresses.

verses.text_plain: He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death, and brake their bands in sunder.
verses.verse_html: 14He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death, and brake their bands in sunder.

verses.text_plain: Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!
verses.verse_html: 15Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!

verses.text_plain: For he hath broken the gates of brass, and cut the bars of iron in sunder.
verses.verse_html: 16For he hath broken the gates of brass, and cut the bars of iron in sunder.

verses.text_plain: Fools because of their transgression, and because of their iniquities, are afflicted.
verses.verse_html: 17Fools because of their transgression, and because of their iniquities, are afflicted.

verses.text_plain: Their soul abhorreth all manner of meat; and they draw near unto the gates of death.
verses.verse_html: 18Their soul abhorreth all manner of meat; and they draw near unto the gates of death.

verses.text_plain: Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble, and he saveth them out of their distresses.
verses.verse_html: 19Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble, and he saveth them out of their distresses.

verses.text_plain: He sent his word, and healed them, and delivered them from their destructions.
verses.verse_html: 20He sent his word, and healed them, and delivered them from their destructions.

verses.text_plain: Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!
verses.verse_html: 21Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!

verses.text_plain: And let them sacrifice the sacrifices of thanksgiving, and declare his works with rejoicing.
verses.verse_html:
22And let them sacrifice the sacrifices of thanksgiving, and declare his works with rejoicing. ▼
▼ rejoicing: Heb. singing

verses.text_plain: They that go down to the sea in ships, that do business in great waters;
verses.verse_html: 23They that go down to the sea in ships, that do business in great waters;

verses.text_plain: These see the works of the Lord, and his wonders in the deep.
verses.verse_html: 24These see the works of the Lord, and his wonders in the deep.

verses.text_plain: For he commandeth, and raiseth the stormy wind, which lifteth up the waves thereof.
verses.verse_html:
25For he commandeth, and raiseth the stormy wind, which lifteth up the waves thereof. ▼
▼ raiseth: Heb. maketh to stand

footnotes.body_html: ▼ raiseth: Heb. maketh to stand

verses.text_plain: They mount up to the heaven, they go down again to the depths: their soul is melted because of trouble.
verses.verse_html: 26They mount up to the heaven, they go down again to the depths: their soul is melted because of trouble.

verses.text_plain: They reel to and fro, and stagger like a drunken man, and are at their wits’ end.
verses.verse_html:
27They reel to and fro, and stagger like a drunken man, and are at their wits’ end. ▼
▼ are…: Heb. all their wisdom is swallowed up

footnotes.body_text: ▼ are…: Heb. all their wisdom is swallowed up
footnotes.body_html: ▼ are…: Heb. all their wisdom is swallowed up

verses.text_plain: Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble, and he bringeth them out of their distresses.
verses.verse_html: 28Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble, and he bringeth them out of their distresses.

verses.text_plain: He maketh the storm a calm, so that the waves thereof are still.
verses.verse_html: 29He maketh the storm a calm, so that the waves thereof are still.

verses.text_plain: Then are they glad because they be quiet; so he bringeth them unto their desired haven.
verses.verse_html: 30Then are they glad because they be quiet; so he bringeth them unto their desired haven.

verses.text_plain: Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!
verses.verse_html: 31Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!

verses.text_plain: Let them exalt him also in the congregation of the people, and praise him in the assembly of the elders.
verses.verse_html: 32Let them exalt him also in the congregation of the people, and praise him in the assembly of the elders.

verses.text_plain: He turneth rivers into a wilderness, and the watersprings into dry ground;
verses.verse_html: 33He turneth rivers into a wilderness, and the watersprings into dry ground;

verses.text_plain: A fruitful land into barrenness, for the wickedness of them that dwell therein.
verses.verse_html:
34A fruitful land into barrenness, for the wickedness of them that dwell therein. ▼
▼ barrenness: Heb. saltiness

verses.text_plain: He turneth the wilderness into a standing water, and dry ground into watersprings.
verses.verse_html: 35He turneth the wilderness into a standing water, and dry ground into watersprings.

verses.text_plain: And there he maketh the hungry to dwell, that they may prepare a city for habitation;
verses.verse_html: 36And there he maketh the hungry to dwell, that they may prepare a city for habitation;

tokens.text: And there he maketh the hungry

verses.text_plain: And sow the fields, and plant vineyards, which may yield fruits of increase.
verses.verse_html: 37And sow the fields, and plant vineyards, which may yield fruits of increase.

verses.text_plain: He blesseth them also, so that they are multiplied greatly; and suffereth not their cattle to decrease.
verses.verse_html: 38He blesseth them also, so that they are multiplied greatly; and suffereth not their cattle to decrease.

tokens.text: them also, so that they are multiplied

verses.text_plain: Again, they are minished and brought low through oppression, affliction, and sorrow.
verses.verse_html: 39Again, they are minished and brought low through oppression, affliction, and sorrow.

verses.text_plain: He poureth contempt upon princes, and causeth them to wander in the wilderness, where there is no way.
verses.verse_html:
40He poureth contempt upon princes, and causeth them to wander in the wilderness, where there is no way. ▼
▼ wilderness: or, void place

footnotes.body_html: ▼ wilderness: or, void place

verses.text_plain: Yet setteth he the poor on high from affliction, and maketh him families like a flock.
verses.verse_html:
41Yet setteth he the poor on high from affliction, and maketh him families like a flock. ▼
▼ from: or, after

verses.text_plain: The righteous shall see it, and rejoice: and all iniquity shall stop her mouth.
verses.verse_html: 42The righteous shall see it, and rejoice: and all iniquity shall stop her mouth.

verses.text_plain: Whoso is wise, and will observe these things, even they shall understand the lovingkindness of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 43Whoso is wise, and will observe these things, even they shall understand the lovingkindness of the Lord.
